claim.claim-text:
1. A system including one or more computing devices connected to a network and configured for prioritizing network content using information captured from interactions of one or more users with a network resource, the system comprising:
a network-connected server that receives captured information from an agent that is provided in at least one computing device of the one or more computing devices connected to the network, wherein the captured information relates to an interaction of a user with the network resource;
an aggregator of the one or more computing devices and associated with the network-connected server that aggregates the captured information with other information related to interactions with a plurality of network resources and that maintains a repository of aggregated captured information;
a prioritizer of the one or more computing devices and associated with the network-connected server that determines relevance of network content based on characteristics of the aggregated captured information; and
wherein the interactions with the plurality of network resources include at least one of a copy and a mouse-over event and the network-connected server are configured to reorder the aggregated captured information, based at least in part, using a statistical analysis correlating the relevance of the network content determined by the prioritizer with a determination of a frequency of access to the network content provided by the plurality of network resources, and wherein the statistical analysis includes at least one of 1) an analysis of the copy event, 2) an identification of a most frequently copied element of the network content provided by the plurality of network resources, 3) a geographic location of the user, 4) a tag cloud identifying the most frequently copied element within a predetermined time period and 5) a frequency of generation of a link associated with the network content.
